				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">4) Unbalanced crafting system. Depending on what tradeskill road you take, you might have an easy time of leveling or a really slow time of leveling. Some tradskillers will find tons of the resources they need, while others will find it much harder to get what they need. Some tradeskill classes have simple combines for good experience and profit to an NPC vendor, while others are forced into relying on other players for materials and quite a bit of low level crafting work just to get raw materials for higher end work. Some crafting professions are totally devoid of recipies, SOE definately released the game with a broken crafting system for some professions, it's a mess. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I disagree that it's a mess.  I've leveled up 4 different artisan classes to 20+, and I don't think they are that different in terms of leveling difficulty.  Alchemists' buffs take more mana, so they are a little slower, but because you need their goods for everything else, I don't think it's an unreasonable trade-off.  Carpenters don't make many useful things, but their boxes are in VERY high demand.  If you gather goods yourself, you'll find plenty of materials for crafting any of the classes, since the best way to gather is to simply harvest every node in an area continuously.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The patch last night shut off selling crafting items to NPC's and appears to have even affected selling common mob drops. Only chest loot can be sold, from reports by some players this morning. This has caused a huge outcry on the EQ II forum and SOE is in full damage control mode (sure to be a Page 80 before the day is done): 
<br />
  </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is serious, I agree.  However I don't think it's unworkable.  I was surprised that you could craft continuously and make money so easily selling to the vendor.  This temporary situation will force players to do some of the artisan quests if they want to make money.  Generally, the artisan quests pay the same amount as you would get if you sold the products to the vendors.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I talked to one guy that had 3 Platinum already, and that is just a huge amount in EQ II. There doesn't seem to be a logical way he could have made the money with out macroing something</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">. 
<br />

<br />
I made 20 gold last night AFK selling. With a second account.  I would have probably made 40.  I don't think it's at all unreasonable that some people (particularly jewelers) have 3 platinum already.
<br />

