			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think the patch will affect me very much as I haven't been selling products to merchants that often.  I'm a level 18 craftsman going woodworking and I've mostly been doing workshop tasks, just to give me some kind of means and motivation to level.  It will probably be an adjustment for a lot of people, but I don't see it as being disastrous.
<br />

<br />
The only places I've noticed a lot of lag is in cities, where there aren't mulitple instances.  All the hunting zones with multiple instances have been fine for me.  In the cities I experience video lag, not network lag, due to too many people in the area.  They really need to make multiple instances for city zones as well, for peak hours.  I don't see how this would be a very hard thing to do for them and it seems like a relatively simple solution to the problem.
<br />

<br />
I agree about the group experience debt.  When in doubt about an encounter I pretty much always attack anyway.  What's the fun if you're going to play with your tail between your legs and your balls tucked in?  I wonder if the same thing happens for raids.  Can you imagine a 24 person xp debt?  I usually sleep it off when it gets too high.
<br />

<br />
I've seen plenty of solo content all over Thundering Steppes and Antonica.  There's very little inside dungeons, but those are geared more toward groups anyway.  If you're looking for solo/duo content I'd suggest looking at some of the book quests.  If you're in Qeynos go to the mage tower in South Qeynos.  One of the mages there sells several books with quests involving solo mobs.  I'd suggest "The Three Keys - Part I" for a good solo/duo quest around 20+ish levels.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28355" target="_blank" class="postlink">Clubbin - EQ</a>
<br />
<a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=225796205" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mathian - EQII</a>
<br />
<a href="http://pub112.ezboard.com/bpoisonarrow5291" target="_blank" class="postlink">Poison Arrow</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
