<br />
Not really.
<br />

<br />
The tradeskill system is pretty sound.  There were some problems with being able to make large amounts of cash from vendor items that have been sold, but there's still the workshop tasks that given decent cash (made 6gp in under an hour on them yesterday).  Really, the bulk of the complaints are pretty much your general unfounded "I want the entire world NOW for zero effort" type of things.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, there's a lot of "junk" recipes but I know the workshop guy wants a lot of them and pays pretty well too...
<br />

<br />

<br />
Shared xp debt:  I disagree that the implementation is fucked up.  You don't get xp debt if you are not in the same zone for a start, so there's part of your problem gone.  Secondly, a single death really isn't much debt at all (under 0.5%) - it's only the group wipes that really hit you hard, especially when people are being dumb about CR and decide to die multiple times rather than revive and collect the shard from the zone door.
<br />

<br />
I've never been a fan of pickup groups and now you just have more incentive to avoid them.  What really sells me on shared xp debt is the fact that morons will now get shitlisted *really* fast.
<br />

<br />

<br />
