I never sell any of my shit to merchants, i either use it, give it to people in exchange for subcombines for myself, or sell it to the population threw my broker. Venders dont offer enough for it to be cost effective atm, and i hope they keep it that way. Selling to venders to earn your profit is retarded, the game is based on a social aspect, and selling to other players makes more sense.
<br />

<br />
I pretty much agree with Ddrak's intire post, hes got it nailed down pretty good. I like the shared exp debt, it makes groups realize that if they fuck up, they will be getting debt just like the people who died. I had a fuckup in my group once that was a complete moron and running around everywhere. We got into an argument that if he didn't shape up wed disband him and get someone else, so he trained the group. He attempted to disband after he trained and learned he couldn't (cant disband or join groups after an encounter has started) and started going apeshit. We all died, he earned 10% exp debt and started shouting how we were hacking o.O. And they said all teh fucktards were going to WoW  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
The only gripe i have about the game is client lag. It seems that the longer i stay on, the more and more i start to lag, mainly while zoning. After about 2 hours i have to log off and relog back on to restart it fresh. Other then that, the game rocks.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
