				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you think the tradeskill system is pretty sound, look at the thread I linked above. LOL, you're in denial or something, there are now 31+ pages worth of complaints, all generated in the last few hours. The developers themselves admit that the system is badly fucked up, so much so that they were forced to shut off selling items to NPC's to stop the exploitation. Some skills aren't even present for certain classes, there are books that drop with zero recipies in them. The system is a mess.
<br />

<br />
It seemed to me that they have fixed the problem with staying on too long. A few weeks ago I took a screen shot of the memory usage when the game was played for about 5 minutes, and after playing it for 2-3 hours. It would go from 512MB ram used to all but a few Kilobytes of all ram used. I haven't noticed that kind of lag for the last week or so, I'll check again.
<br />

<br />
Nektulos on my server was not instanced until last night. I made a mistake saying /who all, it was just /who priest, etc. At one time there was almost 300 people in the zone last weekend and there was no other instance. Last night there was 100+ in both instances but nowhere near 300, so they changed or fixed something. Next up will be Enchanted Lands in a few weeks or a month, we'll see if it gets instanced automatically.
<br />

