			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree that the tradeskill system needs to be looked at but not exactly for the reasons you state.  First off, I am always and I mean ALWAYS in abundance of raw materials that help me make items.  I got to level 10 artisan in a matter of days.  I'm now a level 21 armorer.  
<br />

<br />
My issues with the tradeskills are:
<br />

<br />
1. They are forcing you to rely on each other in order to get simple recipes complete.  A bug is currently allowing ALL artisans (of proper level) to scribe volume 10, 20 and 30 books from their various upgraded tradeskill instanced zones.  I have friends who have purchased the scholar's book, vol 10 as well as the craftsman, etc.  When that "bug" gets fixed, I can no longer make my own stroma wash, my own eolith tempers and other very easy items.  I have to rely on people gathering materials and taking the time to make these mundane items FOR me and sell them via a broker.  The only catch is that the prices will eventually get so low via the broker that people will start selling things to NPC merchants instead.  (That said, with Sony goobered up the selling to NPC thing that I just read about, who knows what's going to happen now.)
<br />

<br />
2. Boredom.  Tradeskills suck.  When I gather up 4 stacks of iron and have to make each one into a bar then each one into either chail or sheets, it's freakin mind-numbing.  The process itself takes time.  I usually put in a DVD and go to work for a few hours.  Not my idea of fun.
<br />

<br />
3. Most of the items that I am capable of creating via tradeskills are nowhere near the value that quest items are.  I've started my paladin armor at level 20 and those items far outweigh anything in my recipe book.  I haven't see the next tier yet (carbonite?) so we'll see.  It's easier for me to get a group and knock out 12 defiled knights in Stormhold than it is for me to rush around trying to find people selling via a the broker board who may have the materials I need to make something myself.  
<br />

<br />
Things I DO enjoy about tradeskills?  I have about 7 gold now, just from items I make via tradeskills, things people NEED: i.e. iron sheets, cailun paper, elm quills.  These things sell like hotcakes and I'm only charging 2-3 silver per item listed above.  
<br />

<br />
I don't like the idea of having to rely on others for my materials.  It hinders my process and if anyone here is like me, once they get started on something complex, it's a huge headache to reach a point where you have to stop because you can't make x_item and there's nobody selling it on the broker board.  Stupid stupid stupid.  Give me the essentials to do my freakin' job.<br />_________________<br />Officer of <a href="http://pub86.ezboard.com/bveterancrew" target="_blank" class="postlink">Veteran Crew</a> 
<br />
<img src="http://www.alluveal.com/rose.jpg" border="0" />[/url]</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
