				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Flunkie,
<br />

<br />
That thread has nothing to do with whether the tradeskill system is "a mess" or not.  It's simply people upset that they can't sell stuff to merchants - most of whom aren't really that serious tradeskillers anyway.  I sit in the crafters channel on my server and most people were just resigned to sit it out until they fix it.  To put it simply, the wannabe tradeskillers are far more upset than the real ones that do it for the fun of tradeskilling rather than making a quick buck.
<br />

<br />
The tradeskill system is good in EQ2.  Sure there's a few teething problems but none of it is indicitive of a bad core design.  I'm still having fun tradeskilling even without being able to sell to merchants for a short while.
<br />

<br />
I honestly don't think EL will get that busy.  Most people seem to be making the dive straight for Runnyeye and just bypassing a lot of EL.  Saw a Lv48^^^ mob in Rivervale though - that was interesting...
<br />

<br />
I will say there is a lot of people getting way to up in arms about a minor amount of debt - often to the point that their own actions result in a lot more debt.  Go figure...
<br />

<br />

<br />
Allu,
<br />

<br />
It's the Lv10-19 books that are scribable and is definitely a bug that they've acknowledged and have said they don't intend fixing for a while.  Anything 20+ you have to go to the person with the other skill.  I don't see the problem with having interdependancies in tradeskills.  You don't expect a warrior or rogue to be beating mobs without a healer.  Why would an armorer be making armor without backup?
<br />

<br />
Tradeskills have always been boring, but at least these ones are a little more interesting than EQ1's drag, drag, drag, drag, combine.  Nowhere near as interesting as fighting mobs for me, but good thing to keep up with when I'm sleepy and waiting for the bathroom to come free, or when I log on and am LFG, etc.
<br />

<br />
Dd</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
