				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ddrak I have to respectfully disagree with you that the tradeskill system is not a mess, and I will explain why.  First off let me say this is coming from the eyes of a 33 Weaponsmith, one of the most dependant crafters in the game next to Armorsmiths.  I was also a 27 Weaponsmith in beta.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Those aren't buffs you are using.</span>
<br />
First off those 'buffs' everyone loves to spam ala an EQ1 bard aren't really buffs, it was a counter system designed that was never fully implimented.  You were not intended to spam those counters, only to press them when a counter event happened.  Beghn's 'vision' for this was to reduce the total number of keystrokes per combine since previously you had real buffs with a 18s and 12s duration.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Oh gee golly Joe, ya know what would be fun? Let's scrap the entire system 3 days before release!!</span>
<br />
3 days before release, for some super odd reason the entire crafting system was tossed out, including resale prices, and this new beast was implimented with 0 testing.  Since the skill requirement for harvesting was in you had high lv crafters who couldnt craft to test a single thing and nothing was tested til after release.
<br />

<br />
The sickest result from this 3 day knee jerk reaction is the fact someone in SoE took the recipies for other classes, slapped them in other books and called it dependancy!  Brilliance!  Jewelers, we bestow you with the power to make pommels!  Weaponsmiths!  We bestow you with the power to make boiled hilts and tailored items!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Exploitation for dummies - vol3</span>
<br />
When I entered T3 with just me and Totum having a good 10-15 levels on everyone we noticed something pretty interesting, the ability to make 5 plat an hour by doing harvesting quests.  Go get 15 of each type of item and then trade the item between you for quest credit, which the devs said was perfectly legal, <span style="text-decoration: underline">but the items would not be taken from your inventory</span>.  We did this 10 more times to verify, petitioned, got a canned response about 'thanks for your report, I will pass to the dev team.'  Didnt take the money and the bug stayed in game for about 3 weeks time.  Part of their fix was to remove T4 harvesting quests as well...... thanks Sony!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Further proof we have an absolutley brillant dev on TS...</span>
<br />
Beghn, master of Tradeskills, decided to ask Suleman for his guild level model and impliment it into the tradeskill societies as a means of unlocking 'shaped' items to advance easier.  Unfortunatly he didnt customize it at all and the net result was it would take 100,000 points per person to level the instance (mind you you only get 100 per quest....).  So weeks go by and he changes this to where it is more in line, an instance on Perma hit level 10 tonight and was able to buy t2 shaped items finally.  All in all this has to remind you of old world EQ vs what EQ became, a watered down version in difficulty after the content has been gone thru once.  No high level crafter does society tasks, they pay crap and will never give us a reward for our time spent, only the people who come behind us.  Not to mention that the 'advanced' socities run off tasks that ask for 10 shaped items and pay ass in return.  Why would I give him 10 shaped Feyiron weapons for 2g when I can make 10 Pristine, get more xp from it, and sell for 20g on the open market?
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Ok, I'm shutting up now..</span>
<br />
Just do not get comfortable with this system, the counters will change and the process will change, hopefully for the better.  Those living in this time will just have the hardest lot to work with.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/cjs27/uqua.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
