				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I play with a solid group os long time EQ friends in WoW. I am slightly lower level then they are (a level or 2) and i tend to seem to run slower... but i die ALL the time ! i mean i'll be standing next to someone and a bear will vaporize out of the middle of nowhere specifically to attack me. Normal and par for the course ? i think so, but a shared exp debit would probably make the druid be sure to watch my health a little more.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Even though this is an EQ2 thread, i had to remark.  Why would they implement a shared xp debt.  There is no xp loss, unless you use the spirit healer which is rare.  I don't know how you are dieing so much as a priest, but that's a whole other can of worms.  Make power word: shield, fade, renew, or flash heal your friend as the situation dictates.  Hell, use psychic scream or mind control for fun <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Also, there is no speed difference between players of different levels.  The differences occur if a player has a movement buff, a mount, or if they are dazed.  You are probably experience graphic lag.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
