			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's an example of a Tier 3 product that requires multiple classes to make stuff:
<br />

<br />
Carbonite Vanguard Plate Leggings
<br />

<br />
primary component:  Carbonite  Plate
<br />

<br />
secondary components: Carbonite Sheet, 2 Carbonite Studs, Boiled Leather Harness
<br />

<br />

<br />
Carbonite Plate = Carbonite Bar + Neolith Temper (armorer makes)
<br />
Carbonite Sheet = Carbonite Bar + Neolith Temper (armorer makes)
<br />
Carbonite Stud = Carbonite Bar + Neolith Temper (Carpenter makes)
<br />
Leather Harness = Stretch of Boiled Leather + Thykaloid (sp) Resin (Tailor Makes) 
<br />

<br />
Carbonite Bar = Carbonite Cluster + Neolith Temper (several classes)
<br />
Stretch of Boiled Leather = Sullied Medium Quality Pelt + Thykaloid Wash (several classes)
<br />

<br />
Neolith Temper = Carbonite, Gold, or Agate +water (alchemist)
<br />
Thykaloid resin and wash = belladonna root + water (alchemist)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Chainmail pieces require patterns made by scribes, but the components for the patterns are made by woodworkers.
<br />

<br />
Rhodric</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
